<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm">
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Circular_area">
 <b>Circular_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/> containing information necessary to determine the two-dimensional area of a circle. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Circular_area.radius">
the <b>radius</b> specifies a <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Circular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Circular_area.centre">
the <b>centre</b> specifies a <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>Circular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area">

An <b>Elliptic_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/>. It is the surface area of an ellipsis.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area.semi_axis_2">
the <b>semi_axis_2</b> specifies a <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Elliptic_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area.semi_axis_1">
the <b>semi_axis_1</b> specifies a <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Elliptic_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area.position">
the <b>position</b> specifies an <express_ref linkend="Layered_2d_shape:arm:Layered_2d_shape_arm.Axis_placement_2d"/> for the <b>Elliptic_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Polygonal_area">
A <b>Polygonal_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/> that is has three distinct points as boundaries in the same plane. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Polygonal_area.bounds">
the <b>bounds</b> specifies the role of a <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>Polygonal_area</b>. There shall be three or more  <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for a <b>Polygonal_area</b>. No  <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> shall be specified more than once as a <b>bounds</b> for a particular <b>Polygonal_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d">
A <b>Primitive_2d</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>. A <b>Primitive_2d</b> may be one of a <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Circular_area"/>, an <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Polygonal_area"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area">
A <b>Rectangular_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area.y">
the <b>y</b> specifies a <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Rectangular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area.x">
the <b>x</b> specifies a <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Rectangular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area.position">
the <b>position</b> specifies an <express_ref linkend="Layered_2d_shape:arm:Layered_2d_shape_arm.Axis_placement_2d"/> for the <b>Rectangular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>
